(Section 4. Privacy and Records) Tj
T*
(Tenant personal information is stored only as required for lease administration and legal compliance.) Tj
T*
(Access to tenant records is restricted to authorized property management staff.) Tj
T*
(Tenants may request a copy of their records by written request; response within 14 days.) Tj
T*
(Records are retained for seven \(7\) years after lease termination, then securely destroyed.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Section 5. Lease Termination) Tj
T*
(Either party may terminate at the end of the lease term with 60 days written notice.) Tj
T*
(Early termination by the tenant incurs a fee equal to two months of rent unless a qualified replacement tenant is found.) Tj
T*
(Termination by the landlord for cause requires written notice and any cure period required by Texas law.) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
